##Through the epidemic, a "Pinkerton" of 48 hours

Vicechina  

Function description, different color vision

The Circle of friends was located in the Arctic Circle at the beginning of the New Year: snow-covered glaciers, dark blue waves crashing on the deck, a kind of sad sound. Katsura writes, "The captain told me that today is actually a good day for Norwegians. Life is hard, Life is always hard.Life is always hard, but I have to face it bravely. In the New Year, I hope everyone can ride the waves and take the joy in Life. "

Not long after that, he received a message on Wechat, hot and tense all of a sudden in the cold weather, that is about the domestic epidemic news. For a media man, it was a trail, but he decided not to be a media man -- a friend's call to help became a "mission" for him to participate directly in donations and rescue operations.

The next day, he set off for home. He and his team mates will act as independent "observers" and organizers to help deliver a truckload of relief supplies to Wuhan. According to his introduction, this is Wuhan after the first successful arrival of a batch of medical supplies.

##

On January 26, five days after academician Zhong Nanshan confirmed the "human-to-human transmission" , and three days after Wuhan issued its first notice of "closing the city to traffic" in the middle of the night. All is still unclear, and even more foggy: How big is the gap in medical prevention and control supplies? At present, what is the most scarce material in Wuhan Hospital, protective equipment or medical equipment? What are the channels for giving and how to do it effectively and in an organized way? Should non-governmental assistance be co-operated with the authorities, given full authority to the Red Cross or supervised for distribution into the Treasury?

When Jiaqiu received the news from friends on January 26, one side was in urgent need of medical supplies to arrive in Wuhan in Jiangsu, the other side was overloaded with hospitals and health care workers in Hubei, in between are the rigorous and complicated procedures, the passage of time and the need to cross the two thousand Li. How can we get the goods to Hubei as soon as possible?

"Many years of first-line donation experience, everything to do, the ability to solve the problem, " Jia Qiu described himself and his team "Real Action Alliance" partners. The number of confirmed cases and deaths is increasing in real time dynamics, jiachu and the team broke down the task into a series of tense steps along the timeline: researching and communicating hospital needs, identifying the recipient hospital, going through the formalities, getting a pass, coordinating with the Red Cross, transporting, arriving at the hospital, monitoring late assignments. After the goods on the road to cross 2238 km, Jia Qiu found a suitable role for his said: "Darts Division. ".

Back in Beijing on January 27th, on a train from Beijing to Hefei on January 29th, at the corner of the deserted square in South Station, Jia Qiu rode the only shared bike in sight to join the drivers. The masters drove a 7.6 m long truck from Changzhou, Jiangsu Province, inside are urgent supplies from Jingzhou City Chest Hospital, Wuhan Tongji Hospital, Huoshenshan Hospital under construction and Wuhan Lung Hospital: 200 Compression atomizers and 20,000 sets of simple sprayers.

"Big trucks can't drive into the core, there's no taxis or buses, and there's a shared bike. " (all images from Cartier)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
NEBULIZER therapy is an important and effective form of respiratory disease therapy and is often used as an adjunct to clinical therapy. "The fifth edition of the new pneumonia diagnosis and treatment program" mentioned that there is no confirmed effective antiviral treatment program, it is recommended to try A-interferon nebulized inhalation; at the same time, nebulized inhalation of expectorants can help patients to expectorate, to improve the clinical symptoms such as breathlessness and wheezing. Aerosol inhalation has certain effect on competing with NCP for treatment time and reducing the incidence of clinical complications.

In other words, the supplies could provide much-needed combat support for first-line treatment.

From the Lotus highway to the shanghai-chongqing highway, the road from Hefei to Wuhan is dark at night. The truck's suspension steel plates had no way of cushioning it from the jolting cab, and "epidemic prevention, anti-pneumonia" slogans flew by, but hardly a car. From the end of the ice-covered world to the night of the inland crisis, the change of vision in the last two or three days seemed unreal to Katchel when she was empty, but most of the time, "The only thing on my mind is to get this done quickly and efficiently. "

A rough, dark night on the highway

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Just met, Jia Qiu felt the two drivers of concern, gave them some knowledge about pneumonia, and told them not to leak their "media man" identity. Along the way, all wearing masks, protective masks and gloves, they ate fried rice in the service area at noon and a bucket of instant noodles in the evening in another service area.

"But I can feel the teachers are very proud of this trip. They posted the route on their friends' circle the day before, " said Jia Qiu.

The truck kept going, and the two drivers took turns. In the cramped back seat of the cab and Corridor connection, the driver took a brief break from the shaking, and she spent a sleepless night in the passenger seat. On the morning of January 30th, at dawn, The van finally arrived at the Red Cross warehouse -- a Hall of the Wuhan International Expo Center.

Inventory, transit system registration, unloading, invoicing procedures, open out of the city Bar, Wuhan Red Cross grass-roots workers working around the clock. The workers are faced with all kinds of materials collected from all over the country to Wuhan. They are working day and night to check whether they are in compliance with the regulations, statistics and archiving. During storage and transportation, Jia Qiu noticed the masks worn by grass-roots personnel, "their masks are too worn and too thin to be useful. When I asked them why they didn't wear better masks, they said good masks should be left for the medical staff, who need them the most. "

"This is the real line that I see, " Ms. Katchoo said. Over the past few days, the Red Cross has been mired in a whirlpool of public opinion. "We can question the poor level of governance and inefficient management in the work of the Red Cross, but the staff at the grass-roots level are really too hard, they are too hard. ". "You're a hub, a hub, and if you get infected, the whole donor system could collapse, " Ms. Katz told them, with great urgency and seriousness. Later, Jiachu noticed that some people change a better mask, but constantly into the traffic, help unloading a few grass-roots personnel or illegal masks wear.

Supplies arrive at the Red Cross warehouse

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Along the way, as she unloaded from the warehouse to the workshop, she observed that the quality of donated supplies was uneven, that a large number of masks did not meet the standards, and that there was a huge accumulation of unheard-of health products. "I don't know what will happen to these sub-standard items with limited capacity and administrative resources, but that's what everyone wants. "

The full delivery time for the first stop is 1 hour and 40 minutes. 100 compressed atomizers and 10,000 simple sprayers will be smoothly received by the Wuhan Red Cross Society, 20 percent of which will be directed by the Red Cross to Tongji Hospital, and the remaining cargo will be temporarily handed over to the headquarters for safekeeping.

The van keeps moving. Four hours later, 60 compression nebulizers and 6,000 simple sprayers arrived in Jingzhou and were delivered directly to Jingzhou Chest Hospital, as confirmed by the Red Cross and the CDC. RAQM Ithnayn，Al Maḩaţţah(Number Two Station) takes two hours. Jingzhou Chest Hospital said the atomizer was urgently needed and would be deployed among Jingzhou hospitals according to the development of the disease.

At 6 pm, the truck arrived near Wuhan's Huoshenshan Hospital. Due to the traffic jam (there was a construction site conflict on the same day) and the Huoshenshan warehouse was near full capacity, Jia Qiu passed the agreement of the Red Cross, the plan was changed to send the remaining 40 compression atomizers and 4,000 simple sprayers back to the Wuhan Red Cross second temporary warehouse. The final phase of unloading, inventory, modification and recording takes two hours, and the Red Cross warehouse is more crowded than it is in the morning.

At the Jingzhou Chest Hospital, the director, the doctors, the nurses, everyone was helping with supplies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the early morning hours of January 31st, those who had successfully unloaded all their supplies could not relax, the tension of stress was gone, and fatigue and fear emerged without a sound. Any luck getting out of town? Are you infected? Will they be quarantined? The two drivers had a long discussion about these concerns. In order to reduce the possibility of infection, they did not stay overnight, decided to drive out of Hubei overnight, home after the initiative to report, the start of isolation. If the journey is inevitable, the return journey is somewhat fatalistic.

Although the aid entered Hubei free of charge on the expressway, Jia Qiu's car was charged more than 700 tolls on the way out. The truck was finally stopped at the exit of the Jintan District highway in Jiangsu Province. On second thought, they chose to return to the city of Changzhou before returning to the territory. On Feb. 1, Jiachu returned to Beijing and began isolating himself (his diary will go online this Saturday in "Bie something else") .

The return journey needs "the blood" the driver master

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The 48-hour "escort" ended, but the "Pinkerton" work did not stop. As the organizer and observer of the trip, Jia Qiu has done the remote tracking of the Red Cross late distribution and material trans-shipment.

On January 31,20 compressed nebulizers and 2000 sprayers (children) have been sent to Tongji Hospital (Guanggu) from Wuhan Red Society and put into storage. On the same day, 40 compression atomizers and 4000 simple sprayers (adults) were sent to the temporary warehouse of Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital by Wuhan Red Society. On February 1, all the remaining materials -- 80 condensing atomizers and 8000 simple sprayers -- were sent to Wuhan Lung Hospital by Wuhan Red Society and put into storage.

With regard to the obstacles encountered in private donations and rescue operations, "civil society and the government need channels of dialogue, a unified platform for information exchange, and agreed rules of procedure and action, " she said. Officials need to cede some power, and civic organizers need to regain trust and reach out to officials. "

"only reason can do things and reduce the waste of social resources. "

In addition to rationality, experience is also needed. "those who have experience in giving should share it as much as possible and don't let it lead US astray, " he said. During the days of self-isolation he worked in bed, answering messages, writing articles, doing monitoring, feeling busier than usual.

At present, Jia Qiu's "Real Action Alliance" observation mission is through the "often love channel" to focus on raising the second batch of materials: For the new diagnostic kits. Hubei Province has implemented the policy of testing the kits first and then declaring them. Jia Qiu and the team have also invited a number of international experts to assist in testing the efficacy of the kits. If the quality is truly reliable, they will communicate with the local coordinating department to promote community acceptance, and find the best way to distribute it.

At the same time, the mission brought together a group of national experts in public health and social governance to study and discuss epidemic prevention issues in real time with experts from the United States and India, and to provide strategic advice to professional bodies, and promote the Chinese Academy of Sciences psychological remote psychological assistance and front-line docking.

On the way back from Jiangsu to Beijing, Jia Qiu saw snow again. A few houses occasionally flashed by among the flying poplars, and the snow lingered on the red-tiled roofs. It had been several days since the beginning of spring, and his self-isolation had come to an end when the time of rain came. Until then, he won't just wait.
